4 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Definitions. For the purposes of [sections 1 through 8], the following
5 definitions apply:
6 (1) "Age-restricted sales venue" means a location or business that is open to the public and
7 prohibits entry of people under 18 years of age. The term may include but is not limited to a:
8 (a) bar, tavern, cocktail lounge, brewery, winery, distillery, nightclub, or any other location where
9 alcohol is served to the public for consumption on the licensed premises under Title 16;
10 (b) liquor store;
11 (c) casino;
12 (d) dispensary licensed under Title 16, chapter 12;
13 (e) adult entertainment venue; and
14 (f) location where vapor products are sold to the public.
15 (1)(2) (a) "Alternative nicotine product" means any manufactured noncombustible product containing
16 nicotine derived from tobacco that is intended for human consumption, whether chewed, absorbed, dissolved,
17 or ingested by any other means. The term includes synthetic nicotine and synthetic nicotine products.
18 (b) The term does not include a tobacco product, A CIGARETTE AS DEFINED IN 16-11-102 OR 16-11-
19 402, a vapor product, or a product regulated as a drug or device by the United States food and drug
20 administration under Chapter V of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act.
21 (2)(3) (a) "Vapor product" means a noncombustible product that may contain nicotine and that uses a
22 heating element, power source, electronic circuit, or other electronic, chemical, or mechanical means,
23 regardless of shape or size, to produce vapor from a solution or other substance. The term includes an
24 electronic cigarette, electronic cigar, electronic cigarillo, electronic pipe, or similar product or device and a vapor
25 cartridge or other container that may contain nicotine in a solution or other form that is intended to be used with
26 or in an electronic cigarette, electronic cigar, electronic cigarillo, electronic pipe, or similar product or device.
